==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gauged
<hw>Gauged</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. a.</pos> <def>Tested or measured
by, or conformed to, a gauge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gauged brick</b></col>, <cd>brick molded, rubbed, or cut
to an exact size and shape, for arches or ornamental work.</cd> --
<col><b>Gauged mortar</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Gauge stuff</cref>, under
<er>Gauge</er>, <pos>n.</pos></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gauger</ent>⟦br⟧
